This practice is transforming my life. Thank you, Adriene, for being such a loving and gentle guide to calm and balance for so many of us. I can confidently say, before I tried yoga a couple of months ago, I just felt like I couldn't catch up with life—the postpartum depression was getting out of hand. Now, despite being sick and injured on and off for months, I feel so much more in-sync. Coupled with a couple of other healthy habits and changes I've made (including using these times to connect with Holy Spirit and the power flowing in and through each one of us—Jesus!), yoga has been an integral key to consistent calm and joy as I take on my day-to-day. I'm happy to say, I positively look forward to each practice because I KNOW I will feel great and my entire day will be transformed by the balance and mental calm I experience every time, without fail! Even the mundane, difficult, or previously stress-inducing tasks become mellowed and my approach can be even and peaceful while facing them. Thank you thank you thank you!!

Here in Mexico we have a thing called "cabañuelas" which is an old traditional system of predicting the weather of the whole year by observing everyday's weather from january 1st to 12th. So, if january the 1st was cold, it will be a cold january, if january 2nd was windy, so will be february, january 3th more sunny, that's how it will be all march, and so on. It might seem silly, but in sometimes it works. I'd like to think the same with this Breath program: from the running of days, practices have been easier, richer, and lighter to me, hopefully for everyone, that I wish this is how is going to be 2021 from here to december for everyone outhere who are fighting, waiting and suffering, things will be better!

ooh that first pose. i'm a mind-over-heart, intellect-over-emotion kind of person, often shut off from my feelings and therefore hesitant to embrace some of adriene's words about self-love. but oh boy, just taking that pose - hands over heart, head slightly lowered - made me realize just how vulnerable i'm feeling tonight. i came home from my doctor's appointment today with a phone number i can call to seek assessment for a mental health issue. i spent most of this evening trying to talk myself out of it, convincing myself that it'll be too hard, too embarassing, that i'm just overreacting and i'll waste everyone's time. but that pose made me feel like i was cradling myself. i could have stayed there for the full twenty minutes, feeling - honestly, for the first time - what it's like to embrace myself and care for myself, completely and without qualification. that's the cheesiest thing i've ever written but it's completely true! and then following it up with that confident, powerful flow ... yeah, this one was well-timed.

✅ Day 11

Each day get better & better! Not only the evolution of the practice Adriene is sharing with us all, but how I am reconnecting to my body, feeling muscles that I forgot I had & building strength. Thank you Adriene, Benji and all of you out there practicing with me. I feel you!! 🙏🏼🤗🥰

My two cats joined for this practice.  Just as I did the first forward fold one of them walked between my legs and came for a kiss 😍 My naughty kitten didnt want me to do a shavasana today, too much playing to do!

Never thought I’d say it Adriene lol, but the knee to nose, right arm and now left arm aren’t difficult for me anymore. I’m not sure if that is thanks to my strength training program, or I’m now getting to an advanced level in Yoga, but it’s really exciting. I have practiced and studied Yoga now on and off for about 10 years, you have inspired me to get certified, and some day teach! But first I need to get a job in my field (IT), find a teaching program and then teach! Thank you for teaching us, encouraging us and being with us during this time when some days it feels like all hope is lost. 

It’s not. God gave us an Adriene, and she is built to give, and restore us with her unique Yoga teaching. I love when you joke, or start singing. One day my partner said (while he was in our bedroom), “that doesn’t sound like Yoga in there” (while I was in our living room), and I just giggled. 

I hope you have a great day Adriene! And to everyone reading, keep practicing, I am proof that you can start as a beginner and progress. And that some days even a more advanced yoga practitioner falls, or makes mistakes, we are human too! 

Namaste & May you be happy 🌸 
Val

I still couldn’t sit cross legged for months after that. My hips are back to being very flexible, but I have fears of hurting them again. Adriene, your directions for most poses help to strengthen muscles around the hip joint. So I feel very safe following your voice.
